<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-720-466  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 720 466.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  July 30 1990 v7 n29 p12(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sun looks to boost relational database integration. (SimplifySQL)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sun Microsystems Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   SimplifySQL (Data base management system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware PackagesStructured Query LanguageRelational Data Bases.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Sun looks to boost relational database integrationandM;MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif.andP;  -- Sun Microsystems is attempting to woo databaseusers to its workstation platform with the release of an enhanced version ofSimplifySQL, an Open Look product designed to simplify the use of relationaldatabases from Oracle, Ingres and Sybase.andM;An earlier version of the product for Ingres was released last fall byIngres, which developed the product with Sun.andM;The tools offered under SimplifySQL enable users to create databases easily,formulate queries and generate reports, according to Sun officials.andM;&quot;This product offers ease of use to people who are not conversant or expertswith the different databases,&quot; said Jon Richards, Sun's product manager forSimplifySQL.andM;&quot;Customers have found that databases in general and SQL in particular arepretty hard to understand and work with.andP;  The SQL for different databases isalways different, and SQL is bad enough,&quot; he said.andM;&quot;There's a difference also in the report writing language, and it'scumbersome.andP;  With SimplifySQL, all the user needs to know is where the datais and how to point and click,&quot; he said.andM;Four modules are included with SimplifySQL.andP;  Session Manager allows users toselect the database they want to use; DataBrowse lets users create databasequeries by pointing and clicking on desired data fields; a graphical reporteditor called ReportWrite lets users create customized reports; andSchemaDesign lets users graphically create, view and modify database layouts.andM;Richards said that Sun ultimately seeks to access multiple databases,including Rdb, across multiple platforms with SimplifySQL.andM;&quot;Right now, we can access these products on Suns, but the next level is toaccess those and other databases running on other machines,&quot; Richards said.andO;&quot;We theoretically should be able to do that already, though we're in theprocess of confirming it.andP;  We'd like to be able to let Sun users access anydatabase wherever it is--on a Sun, on a VAX or on a mainframe.&quot;andM;SimplifySQL is priced at $995 and will be available in October.andM;For additional product information, Sun Microsystems Inc. can be contacted at2550 Garcia Ave., Mountain View, CA 94043, (415) 960-1300.andO;</TEXT></DOC>